{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, meaningfulness can be directly defined or assessed using human cognitive knowledge.",
    "Meaningfulness can refer to semantical segmentation methods such as SLIC [144,187], LI-SLIC [188], SEAL [189], SSN [190], and FCN [191] from a functional standpoint.",
    "CompletenessExplanation sufficiency or completeness indicate whether the proposed explanation is sufficient to fully interpret the model or whether additional efforts are required [25,105].",
    "It collaborates to answer the following questions: o Do end-users obtain a complete interpretation of the model?",
    "o Is it possible to provide additional explanation?"
  ]
}